# Shiba Studio environment overrides — copy to .env.local and fill in.
# .env.local is gitignored, so your secrets stay on your machine.

# --- Google Drive sign-in (optional: makes Drive zero-setup for every user) ---
# Create ONE OAuth client in Google Cloud Console:
#   APIs & Services → Credentials → Create OAuth client ID → Web application
#   Authorized redirect URI: http://localhost:3000/api/google-oauth/callback
#   (also enable the Google Drive API for the project)
# Paste the client's ID and secret below. When set, the Capabilities → Google
# Drive card shows "Sign in with Google" with no per-user setup — users just
# sign in and approve. Leave blank to have each user add their own client under
# the card's Advanced section.
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=

# --- Optional runtime overrides (see docs/configuration.md) ---
# SHIBA_DATA_DIR=
# SHIBA_SECRET_KEY=
# SHIBA_GIT_COMMIT=
